					<description><![CDATA[I attended a talk on managing stress by a clinical psychologist two days ago. Towards the end of her talk, she played a Progressive Muscle Relaxation guided meditation mp3. I felt instantly relaxed just after 10 minutes. She suggested that we all try it at home as a way to wind down at night. I tried it for two nights in a row and I believe my sleep quality has improved since. So I recommend guided PMR meditation before bed time. There are so many to choose from on YouTube. You won&#039;t go very wrong if you pick one of those with the most views. Try it!]]></description>
			<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>I attended a talk on managing stress by a clinical psychologist two days ago. Towards the end of her talk, she played a Progressive Muscle Relaxation guided meditation mp3. I felt instantly relaxed just after 10 minutes. She suggested that we all try it at home as a way to wind down at night. I tried it for two nights in a row and I believe my sleep quality has improved since. So I recommend guided PMR meditation before bed time. There are so many to choose from on YouTube. You won&#8217;t go very wrong if you pick one of those with the most views. Try it!</p>
