					<description><![CDATA[In reply to &lt;a href=&quot;https://jamesclear.com/sleep-levers#comment-11622&quot;&gt;Chris Justin&lt;/a&gt;.

Sometimes your mind tries to not forget something because it is important. Maybe journaling can help. Write everything down that&#039;s in your head every evening to stop your thoughts cycling around these problems.

I wake up at night if I keep my socks on.

Start making experiments: Try to leave the window open or closed. Try leaving your socks on or not leaving &#039;em on. Try to eat your last meal sooner. Try to not drink one hour before sleeptime. Try to drink a tea in the evening. Try what makes sense to you.]]></description>
			<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>In reply to <a href="https://jamesclear.com/sleep-levers#comment-11622">Chris Justin</a>.</p>
<p>Sometimes your mind tries to not forget something because it is important. Maybe journaling can help. Write everything down that&#8217;s in your head every evening to stop your thoughts cycling around these problems.</p>
<p>I wake up at night if I keep my socks on.</p>
<p>Start making experiments: Try to leave the window open or closed. Try leaving your socks on or not leaving &#8217;em on. Try to eat your last meal sooner. Try to not drink one hour before sleeptime. Try to drink a tea in the evening. Try what makes sense to you.</p>
